title: Found out you're paid less than your colleagues? Here's what you can do about ‘wage compression’
description: Wage compression can occur when long-term employees and their wages fail to keep pace with the market — while newer employees are paid the market rate.

title: Jamie Dimon warns souring commercial real estate loans could threaten some banks
description: U.S. banks have experienced historically low loan defaults over the last few years due to low interest rates and the flood of Covid stimulus money.

title: Here’s what Pfizer and Moderna say is next for their Covid vaccines
description: Pfizer and Moderna are ushering in a new era for their Covid shots that aims to simplify what people need to do to coexist with the virus.

title: Biden and McCarthy to meet on the debt ceiling with only 10 days until U.S. risks default
description: White House negotiators and representatives of House Speaker Kevin McCarthy resumed debt ceiling talks Monday morning in the Capitol.

title: Fed's Kashkari says a June pause on rates wouldn't indicate an end to hiking cycle
description: Kashkari told CNBC on Monday he's open to holding off on another rate hike, but cautioned against reading too much into a pause.

title: Isolating China will be 'impossible and dangerous,' analyst says, as the G-7 gets tough on Beijing
description: An analyst has warned it is "impossible" and "dangerous" to isolate Beijing, after the G-7 issued its strongest ever message to China over the weekend.

title: GM will introduce an all-electric Cadillac Escalade 'IQ' later this year
description: GM said the new SUV will be called the "Escalade IQ," which continues Cadillac's EV naming strategy that so far includes the Lyriq and upcoming Celestiq.

title: Kurt Cobain's smashed Fender guitar sells for almost $600,000
description: Kurt Cobain's smashed Fender Stratocaster guitar sold at auction for $595,900 on Saturday, more than 10 times its original estimate.

title: Meta fined a record $1.3 billion over EU user data transfers to the U.S.
description: Meta has been fined a record 1.2 billion euro ($1.3 billion) by European privacy regulators over the transfer of EU user data to the U.S.

title: Fintech firm Wise's shares fall after announcing CFO is resigning, CEO to go on leave
description: Shares of British fintech Wise sank Monday after announcing its CFO Matt Briers is leaving the company while CEO Kristo Kaarman is to go on paternity leave.

title: Ryanair reports bumper profit on 'favorable' fuel hedges, sees major industry consolidation
description: Ryanair CEO Michael O'Leary said the airline's "industry leading" fuel hedging contributed significantly to its full-year profit.

title: European officials are quietly preparing for the possibility Biden loses the next election
description: The EU, a group of 27 nations, was openly thrilled with the election of Joe Biden in late 2020 after four challenging years under the presidency of Trump.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Debt ceiling detours
description: The good news: Biden will meet McCarthy in person later today to discuss the debt ceiling. The bad: There’s no telling how the talks will proceed.

title: China chip stocks rally after Beijing said U.S. chip giant Micron is 'major security risk'
description: Shares of its South Korean and Chinese rivals surged on Monday, some as much as up to 8% higher.

title: Wall Street is bullish on Chinese tech firms, even as recovery is uneven
description: Analysts are bullish on China's tech industry even if recovery is not uniform across different tech companies.

title: Norway faces backlash from campaigners for 'reckless' pursuit of Arctic oil and gas
description: The Norwegian government says it is seeking to maintain Europe's energy security by exploring the Barents Sea for further resources.

title: America's Got Talent judge Simon Cowell says this advice from his dad inspired his success
description: Music mogul-turned-multimillionaire Simon Cowell said his career success was inspired by an early piece of advice from his father.

title: Singapore Prime Minister Lee Hsien Loong tests positive for Covid
description: The Singapore Prime Minister said Monday in a Facebook post he has tested positive for Covid-19 for the first time, after returning from recent state visits.

title: Southeast Asia’s worst-performing stock market is UBS’s ‘top pick’
description: There's plenty of optimism about Thailand as its tourism potential, but political headwinds could still be a game-changer, says Kelvin Tay from UBS Global Wealth Management.

description: The impact of a widening rift between the U.S. and China may lead to further damage, economists warn.
